Puzzle 7 | (3 Bulbs and 3 Switches)
Difficulty Level : Easy
Last Updated : 24 Aug, 2021
There is a room with a door (closed) and three light bulbs. Outside the room, there are three switches, connected to the bulbs. You may manipulate the switches as you wish, but once you open the door you canâ€™t change them. Identify each switch with its bulb. All bulbs are in working condition.
Solution:
Let the bulbs be X, Y, and Z 
Turn on switch X for 5 to 10 minutes. Turn it off and turn on switch Y. Open the door and touch the light bulb. 
1. the light is on from the bulb, it is Y 

Now we will check other two off bulbs 
2. the bulb which is hot, it is X 
3. the bulb which is cold, it is Z  
 

